result.execSummary:
The defendant Vincent O Gammel was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

10:43 Defendant Vincent O Gammel in court with attorney Robert A Gardner.  Kelly A Lehn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Not guilty plea entered.  Bond continued.

10:19 Defendant Vincent O Gammel in court with attorney Robert A Gardner.  Kelly A Lehn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Bren Derringer is sworn as a witness.  Testifies to his employment with Wood County Sheriff's Dept.  On 06/04/14 at 12:41 pm he performed a traffic stop in the City of Wis Rapids.  Driver was identified by driver's license as Vincent Gammel.  Identifies Vincent Gammel in the courtroom.  Describes Gammel's behavior upon contact and belief that Gammel maybe involved in the sale or exchange of illegal substances based on behaviors.  Describes observations of the vehicle.  Canine officer was brought to scene and walked around vehicle.  Canine indicated positive for illegal substances.  Testifies to search of vehicle and items found.  Testifies to testing the green leafy substance and to the results being positive for THC.  Testifies to his basis for charging Gammel  with Possession with Intent to Deliver THC.  

Atty Gardner cross examines the witness.  Describes stop and basis for stop.  Car did not register to Gammel.  Testifies to passenger in vehicle.  Testifies to timeframes.  Testifies to the number of air fresheners in vehicle.  Describes back in the backseat.  Testifies to the location of the child.  Testifies to contact with Gammel's sister in which she indicated that none of the items were hers.  Testifies to the amount of money Gammel had on him.  

Atty Gardner argues that the testimony does not support a Possession with Intent charge and moves to dismiss the felony level offense.  Court denies the motion.

Court finds probable cause and proceeds to ARGN.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for July 25, 2014 at 10:00 am.
Preliminary hearing and Arraignment on June 25, 2014 at 10:15 am.
Defendant Vincent O Gammel in court, in custody.  Kelly A Lehn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
